<p><a name="External_links" id="External_links"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Telecommunications_data_retention&amp;action=edit&amp;section=21" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Bowden, Caspar "Closed Circuit Television For Inside Your Head: Blanket Traffic Data Retention and the Emergency Anti-Terrorism Legislation" Computer and Telecommunications Law Review, March 2002, <a href="http://www.law.duke.edu/journals/dltr/articles/2002dltr0005.html" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.law.duke.edu/journals/dltr/articles/2002dltr0005.html" rel="nofollow">[6]</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.edri.org/issues/privacy/dataretention" class="external text" title="http://www.edri.org/issues/privacy/dataretention" rel="nofollow">EDRI news tracking page on data retention</a> (current)</li>
<li>Walker, C., &amp; Akdeniz, Y., "Anti-Terrorism laws and data retention: war is over?" (2003) Northern Ireland Legal Quarterly, 54(2), Summer, 159-182,<a href="http://www.cyber-rights.org/documents/data_retention_article.pdf" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.cyber-rights.org/documents/data_retention_article.pdf" rel="nofollow">[7]</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.epic.org/privacy/intl/data_retention.html" class="external text" title="http://www.epic.org/privacy/intl/data_retention.html" rel="nofollow">EPIC data retention page</a> (to 2007)</li>
<li>UK Home Office <a href="http://www.homeoffice.gov.uk/inside/consults/closed/papers2003.html" class="external text" title="http://www.homeoffice.gov.uk/inside/consults/closed/papers2003.html" rel="nofollow">consultation papers</a> on data retention and on access to communications data.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.digitalrights.ie/2006/09/14/dri-brings-legal-action-over-mass-surveillance/" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.digitalrights.ie/2006/09/14/dri-brings-legal-action-over-mass-surveillance/" rel="nofollow">[8]</a>Digital Rights Ireland's challenge against the EU Data Retention Directive and Irish retention legislation on the grounds of European and Irish constitutional law.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.cybertelecom.org/security/records.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.cybertelecom.org/security/records.htm" rel="nofollow">Cybertelecom&#160;:: Records Keeping / Data Retention</a></li>
<li><a href="http://tor.eff.org/" class="external text" title="http://tor.eff.org/" rel="nofollow">TOR project</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.emplaw.co.uk/free/4frame/data/14sep99.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.emplaw.co.uk/free/4frame/data/14sep99.htm" rel="nofollow">Emplaw.co.uk re data protection</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.tkg-verfassungsbeschwerde.de/data_retention_and_human_rights_essay.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.tkg-verfassungsbeschwerde.de/data_retention_and_human_rights_essay.pdf" rel="nofollow">Article "Telecommunications Data Retention and Human Rights: The Compatibility of Blanket Traffic Data Retention with the ECHR"</a> by Patrick Breyer, European Law Journal, May 2005.</li>
</ul>
<p><a href="http://eprints.law.duke.edu/1602/Article" class="external free" title="http://eprints.law.duke.edu/1602/Article" rel="nofollow">http://eprints.law.duke.edu/1602/Article</a> "Protecting Privacy against the Police in the European Union: The Data Retention Directive"] by Professor Francesca Bignami, <a href="/wiki/Chicago_Journal_of_International_Law" title="Chicago Journal of International Law">Chicago Journal of International Law</a>, Spring 2007.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.watsonhall.com/methodology/uk-data-retention-requirements.pl" class="external text" title="http://www.watsonhall.com/methodology/uk-data-retention-requirements.pl" rel="nofollow">UK Data Retention Requirements</a> with full references to legislation, codes of practice, etc.</li>
</ul>


